section*
  code $loinc#67852-4 Hospital Admission evaluation note
  title Admission evaluation
  text """Mrs. Ingrid Arvidson, an 84-year-old Swedish female, was admitted on 2nd February 2025 with bilateral lower limb oedema and progressive dyspnoea. On physical examination, severe bilateral pulmonary crepitations were noted throughout both lung fields. Initial laboratory investigations revealed markedly elevated troponin I at 400 ng/L, strongly suggestive of cardiac pathology.<p/>The clinical picture was consistent with acute decompensated congestive heart failure. The patient was haemodynamically stable on arrival. She was commenced immediately on intravenous diuretic therapy (furosemide) and heart failure medications, and an urgent cardiology consultation was requested."""
