section*
  type procedure
  code $loinc#10185-7 Hospital discharge procedures Narrative
  title Significant Procedures
  text """Cardiac catheterization was performed on Day 2 to confirm aortic valve dysfunction and evaluate coronary anatomy. Aortography showed 3+ to 4+ contrast backflow into a dilated left ventricle consistent with severe aortic regurgitation/stenosis, and left ventricular ejection fraction was estimated at 40%.<p/>Following multidisciplinary heart team review on Day 3, Transcatheter Aortic Valve Implantation (TAVI) was indicated due to advanced patient age and high surgical risk. The procedure was performed successfully between Days 4 and 7 without intraoperative complications. The patient was monitored post-procedurally in the coronary care unit."""
  entry*
    type procedure
    date 2025-02-04
    code $sct#301095005 Cardiac catheterization (procedure)
    status completed
  entry*
    type procedure
    date 2025-02-05
    code $sct#450506006 Transcatheter aortic valve implantation (procedure)
    status completed
  entry*
    type procedure
    date 2025-02-02
    code $sct#47545007 Continuous intravenous infusion therapy (procedure)
    text """Intravenous diuresis with furosemide on admission."""
    status completed
